Cobalt and iron hemes are analogous in many aspects, including the oxygen bonding ability16–18. Recently, we have reported the [Co(TpivPP)(R-Im)(O2)] (R-Im: 1-EtIm or 2-MeHIm; TpivPP = α, α, α, α-tetrakis(o-pivalamidophenyl)porphyrinato) complexes using imidazole cobalt(II) porphyrinates as the starting material, which are all five-coordinate due to the destabilization of the six-coordinate compound by the singly populated \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
