				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$d_{z^2}$$\end{document}dz2 orbital19. Remarkably all the imidazole cobalt(II) porphyrinates are low-spin state (3d7, S = 1/2) regardless of the steric hindrance of the axial ligands20. This is contrasted to iron(II) analogs, the use of hindered imidazole is necessary to prepare the five-coordinate iron(II) porphyrinates, all of which known so far are high-spin (3d6, S = 2)21.

